                <h3>City walls</h3>
                <p>Mrauk U Palace was defended by three city walls.</p>
                </br>
                <h3>Palace enclosure walls</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>(1) Let Sei Kan wall (south side)</li>
                    <li>(2) Anuma wall (south side)</li>
                    <li>(3) Nga Chauk Zey wall (west side)</li>
                    <li>(4) War Zey wall (west side)</li>
                    <li>(5) Yathey Taung wall (west side)</li>
                    <li>(6) Pein Hne Taung wall (west side)</li>
                    <li>(7) Min Tha Kyun wall ( west side)</li>
                    <li>(8) Yey Tagar wall (west side )</li>
                    <li>(9) Shan Taung wall (north side)</li>
                    <li>(10) Chin Kite wall (north side)</li>
                    <li>(11) Min Tha Mee Myaung wall (North side)</li>
                    <li>(12) Thet Ku Mann Aung wall (east side)</li>
